In this article, Vice President Kamala Harris and Congresswoman Mary Gay Scanlon discuss the importance of protecting reproductive rights in the wake of the recent Supreme Court decision on abortion rights. They highlight the need to fight against laws that criminalize healthcare providers and restrict access to reproductive healthcare. They also emphasize the importance of coalition-building and working together to protect these rights. The conversation touches on other issues such as healthcare, equity, and the impact of these decisions on marginalized communities. The Vice President and Congresswoman encourage young people to mobilize and take action to support these rights and urge everyone to participate in upcoming elections to secure legislative protection for reproductive rights.